description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;So, you’re eager to learn more about Older People’s Mental Health / Learning Disability Nursing opportunities at DCHS. Here are some of the reasons we’re unique…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Walton Unit is the only specialist Mental Health Unit purpose designed for older adults with Organic illness in North Derbyshire.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hillside Assessment and Treatment Unit is the only specialist NHS ATU in Derbyshire.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Our dedicated OPMH Walton Unit and Hillside unit provides the highest level of mental health and learning disability care and support to our patients, we are proud to be part of an outstanding trust, as rated by the CQC.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We offer opportunities to develop professionally via our in-house leadership development programmes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;But it’s not just our OPMH service which is impressive; our Trust itself is pioneering in its approach to healthcare. Let us tell you a little more about it…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Derbyshire Community Health Services has been rated as an ‘outstanding’ trust by the Care Quality Commission; we have achieved this by providing high quality patient care within an inclusive organisation that works together and shows care and compassion for each other.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us as one of the largest specialist community NHS providers in the country – one that is also among the very best NHS employers as voted by its own staff and by CQC. DCHS is a top performing NHS Trust that strives for innovation and improvement for the service and individuals that work within it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As well as the usual NHS benefits available to our staff, here are just a few more:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Option to buy up to 10 days additional annual leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free parking at all of our sites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Local attraction discounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff health &amp; wellbeing programmes supported by our award winning wellbeing team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lease car scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relocation package (qualifying criteria)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Right, that’s enough about us… let’s focus on you. Are you…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An experienced health care assistant / care support worker who is Passionate about delivering high quality care to some of the most vulnerable members of our society.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A good communicator who is able to relay information to patients and their loved ones in a sensitive and compassionate way&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;So, are we right for each other? If you think we should talk more, here are the next steps…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contact Julie Thornhill if you have any queries prior to submitting your application or for more information about the role via 01246 515611 or email thornhill@nhs.net&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Submit your application via this advert and our recruitment team will support you through your application.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow us on social media to join in the conversation and gain an insight into life at DCHS - search @DCHSJobs or @DCHStrust on Twitter and Facebook.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Email us if you have any questions about applying for a role peopleresourceteam@nhs.net&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an employee it will be your responsibility to ensure that your behaviour and values reflect those set out in the DCHS Way outlined on our website and in the additional information provided&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Julie Thornhill, Ward Manager - Walton unit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;julie.thornhill@nhs.net, 01246 515611&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Susan Hedley - Ward Manager - Hillside Unit - 01246 565054&lt;/p&gt;
